# Repository Conventions

## Purpose
Establish project-wide coding standards, file organization, and naming conventions.

## Directory Structure
```
src/core/       - Data models, business logic
src/scanner/    - Browser detection, profile resolution
src/execution/  - Deletion engine, backup manager
src/ui/         - PyQt6 GUI components
tests/          - Unit and integration tests
docs/           - Documentation, PRD
scripts/        - Automation scripts
.context/       - Memory Bank
```

## Python Conventions
- Use type hints for all function signatures
- Follow PEP 8 (black formatter, line length 100)
- Dataclasses for data models
- Docstrings for all public classes/functions
- Absolute imports (from src.core import models)

## File Naming
- snake_case for Python files
- PascalCase for classes
- UPPER_CASE for constants
- Test files: test_{module_name}.py

## Commit Messages
```
[module] Brief description

- Detail 1
- Detail 2
```
